    <h2>Non-Buildable Locations</h2>
    <p>These locations have no industry slots. Links passing through them count as 2 segments (double cost).</p>
    <table class="wiki-table">
      <tr><th>Location</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Northwich</td><td>On the Warrington-Ellesmere Port route</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Blackpool</td><td>On the Fleetwood-Preston route</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Southport</td><td>On the Wigan-Liverpool route</td></tr>
    </table>

    <h2>External Ports</h2>
    <p>Permanent port connections on the board edges. Always accessible for selling cotton - no link building needed.</p>
    <table class="wiki-table">
      <tr><th>Port</th><th>Connected To</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Scotland</td><td>Lancaster</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Yorkshire</td><td>Colne, Burnley, Rochdale</td></tr>
      <tr><td>The Midlands</td><td>Ellesmere Port, Stockport</td></tr>
